HEADWORD: Pitch-faced
<hw>Pitch"-faced`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Stone
Cutting)</fld> <def>Having the arris defined by a line beyond which the
rock is cut away, so as to give nearly true edges; -- said of squared
stones that are otherwise quarry-faced.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

